description:
File: lichen/subsys/lichen/app_interface/app_interface.c

The statistics structure contains multiple uint32_t counters. While individual increments are protected by the mutex (lines 222-229, etc.), the copy_stats function (lines 608-619) performs a structure copy under the mutex:

  int lichen_app_interface_copy_stats(struct lichen_app_interface_stats *stats)
  {
      if (stats == NULL) {
          return -EINVAL;
      }
      k_mutex_lock(&s_mutex, K_FOREVER);
      *stats = s_stats;
      k_mutex_unlock(&s_mutex);
      return 0;
  }

This is correct for consistency. However, the test_reset function (lines 622-630) does not reset the test hook variables atomically with the stats reset:

  void lichen_app_interface_test_reset(void)
  {
      k_mutex_lock(&s_mutex, K_FOREVER);
      memset(s_sinks, 0, sizeof(s_sinks));
      memset(&s_stats, 0, sizeof(s_stats));
      s_test_next_location_submit_ret = 0;
      s_test_next_clear_network_ret = 0;
      k_mutex_unlock(&s_mutex);
  }

This is actually fine since all operations are under the same mutex. No bug here - closing as false positive.

Actually, the code is correct. The mutex protects all operations properly.
